🚀 PRD: Vanguard Backend Intelligence System1. Project VisionVanguard is an AI-native volunteer management platform. It solves the "churn" problem by using semantic matching to find the right tasks for the right people and tracking "Engagement Health" via a time-decay scoring algorithm.2. The "Elite" Tech Stack (100% Free)Framework: FastAPI (Python 3.10+)Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL + pgvector)AI Model: sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2Note: This generates 384-dimensional embeddings locally. No OpenAI API keys required.Hosting Target: Render/Railway (Free Tier).3. Database Schema ContextThe Supabase instance is already configured with the following:volunteers: id, full_name, email, bio, skills[], embedding vector(384), engagement_score, last_active_at.tasks: id, title, description, required_skills, task_vector vector(384), status.activity_logs: id, volunteer_id, activity_type, points_awarded.RPC Function: match_volunteers(query_embedding, match_threshold, match_count) which performs cosine similarity search.Database View: volunteer_retention_status which calculates real-time health using: score - (days_inactive * 2).4. Feature Requirements & LogicA. The Embedding Engine (Module 1)On POST /volunteers or POST /tasks, the backend must use the SentenceTransformer model to vectorize the bio or description.This vector must be saved as a list of floats in the database.B. The Routing Engine (Module 2)Endpoint: GET /tasks/{task_id}/matchesLogic: 1. Retrieve the task_vector from the DB.2. Pass that vector to the match_volunteers RPC function in Supabase.3. Return a ranked list of volunteers with a similarity_score.C. The Engagement Pulse (Module 3)Endpoint: POST /logsLogic: When an activity is logged (e.g., "task_completion"), update the volunteer's last_active_at timestamp and increment their engagement_score in the volunteers table.Health View: Expose a GET /volunteers/health endpoint that reads from the volunteer_retention_status view to show who is 'At-Risk'.5. API Endpoints for ImplementationPOST /volunteers: Create profile + Generate 384-dim embedding.POST /tasks: Create task + Generate 384-dim embedding.GET /volunteers: List all volunteers + current health status.GET /tasks/{id}/recommendations: Semantic search for the best volunteers for a task.POST /logs: Record activity and trigger score updates.6. Implementation Notes for CopilotUse sentence-transformers library for local embeddings.Use supabase-py for database interactions.Ensure the model is loaded once at startup (Singleton pattern) to save memory on free-tier hosting.Use .env for SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_KEY.